HEADWORD: Arles
<hw>Arles</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>arrhes</ets>, Scot. <ets>airles</ets>. Cf. <er>Earles
penny</er>.]</ety> <def>An earnest; earnest money; money paid to bind a
bargain.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Arles penny</b></col>, <cd>earnest money given to
servants.</cd> <au>Kersey.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

